article.headline: UCLA 83, Washington 75
article.story:
LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Noelle Quinn had 23 points and nine assists
Saturday to give UCLA its fifth win in six games, an 83-75 victory
over Washington.

Quinn went 10-for-19 from the field and also pulled down eight
rebounds.

Lisa Willis had 16 points and 12 rebounds and Lindsey Pluimer
added 15 points and 12 rebounds for the Bruins (15-9, 10-5), who
pulled within a half-game of the Huskies (16-7, 9-5) for third
place in the Pacific 10 Conference.

Washington is two games behind conference-leading Stanford and a
half-game behind second-place Arizona State.

Cameo Hicks led the Huskies with 21 points, Andrea Plouffe
scored 16, and Breanne Watson had 11 points and 10 rebounds.
